'''Wayne Humfleet''' (born [[July 12]]) is an [[Wikipedia:American|American]] author. For ''[[Star Wars]]'', he authored the short stories "[[Swoop Gangs]]" and "[[Lumrunner]]" with [[John Beyer]], which were published in the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 6|sixth]] and [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 9|ninth]] issues of ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' in [[1995]] and [[1996]], respectively. He also contributed to the 1995 [[West End Games]] [[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game|roleplaying]] sourcebook ''[[Heroes & Rogues]]''.

==Biography==
Wayne Humfleet is an [[Wikipedia:American|American]]<ref name="Nationality-AboutSection" /> author<ref name="Kickstarter" /> who was born on [[July 12]].<ref name="Birthday" /> He<ref name="Pronouns" /> is a lifelong ''[[Star Wars]]'' fan, and his gaming group&mdash;the Rabid Mynocks&mdash;remains active players of [[West End Games]]' [[Wikipedia:D6 System|D6 System]] as of [[2024]].<ref name="Kickstarter" />

Humfleet's first ''Star Wars'' work was "[[Swoop Gangs]]," a short story authored by himself and [[John Beyer]] that was published in the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 6|sixth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' magazine in [[May]] [[1995]]. "Swoop Gangs" introduced the [[in-universe]] [[swoop]] gang [[Rabid Mynocks]],<ref name="Swoop Gangs">{{Journal|6|Swoop Gangs}}</ref> which shares its name with Humfleet's real-world gaming group. He also contributed to ''[[Heroes & Rogues]]'',<ref name="Kickstarter" /> a supplement book released by for use with West End Games ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''<ref name="HR">''[[Heroes & Rogues]]''</ref> on [[December 11]], 1995,<ref name="BN">{{BN|url=w/star-wars-the-roleplaying-game-west-end-games-incorporated/1018175956|text=Star Wars the Roleplaying Game: Heroes & Rogues (Star Wars Supplements Series)|nolive=1}}</ref> though was not credited in the title.<ref name="HR Credit">{{Uncredited|Wayne Humfleet|''[[Heroes & Rogues]]''}}</ref> Humfleet later co-authored the short story "[[Lumrunners]]" with Beyer, which was published in the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 9|ninth issue]] of ''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' and released in [[February]] [[1996]].<ref name="Lumrunners">{{Journal|9|Lumrunners}}</ref> At some point, he adopted the name "Lumrunner" for some of his social media handles.<ref name="Twitter">{{Twitter|username=lumrunner|name=Wayne "Lumrunner" Humfleet|archivedate=20241111221608}}</ref><ref name="Instagram">{{Instagram|username=lumrunner|name=Wayne Humfleet|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/n1f2L}}</ref>

In 2024, Humfleet collaborated with other ''Star Wars'' authors such as [[Bill Smith]], [[Peter M. Schweighofer]], [[Timothy S. O'Brien]], [[Drew Campbell]], and [[Michael Kogge]], having been brought to a project together by former West End Games Creative Director [[Eric S. Trautmann]].<ref name="OtherProject">{{WebCite|url=https://www.drivethrurpg.com/en/product/320518/star-system-every-star-a-destination|text=Star System: Every Star A Destination|archivedate=20240806034521}}</ref>

